[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man dies after crash near Peebles

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An 87-year-old man has died after a crash in the Scottish Borders on Saturday morning.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were called to the collision on the A72 Peebles to Innerleithen road at about 11:10.
Three men - aged 87, 71 and 42 - were taken to hospital. The 87-year-old died a short time later.
Police Scotland appealed for any witnesses to the crash, which involved a red Vauxhall Meriva and a silver Honda CR-V.
